    "created_at": "2014-06-08T06:02:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-08T06:03:14Z",
    "body": "On unix: [POSIX specification](http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/000095399/functions/pthread_attr_getguardsize.html) says default guard size is page size. (And at least on my amd64 linux returns `pthread_attr_getguardsize` returns 4096)\n\nOn windows: native thread has guard page support: see [msdn article](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms686774%28v=vs.85%29.aspx) and [Mark Russinovich's blog article](http://blogs.technet.com/b/markrussinovich/archive/2009/07/08/3261309.aspx).\n",
